('20081028193034', '20080919070322', '20080919070021', 'Nikon AP-8', NULL, '<div class="mosimage_caption">AP-8</div>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />This AP-8 features an engineer&rsquo;s handy automatic level with accuracy of &plusmn;1.5mm in 1km double-run leveling and friction brake for faster operation. Moreover, an endless horizontal drive with control knobs on both sides, water-resistant construction for use under dusty conditions or in light rain, and the option to mount on a flat- or spherical-head tripod all contribute to enhanced operability. Optional diagonal eyepiece lens attachments for use in confined spaces are also available.', '20081028194752-level_ap8_150150x.gif', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<br /><br />Telescope  <br /><br />Tube Length : 7.5 in (190 mm)<br /> Image: erect<br /> Effective diameter of objective: 1.2 in (30 mm)<br /> Magnification: 28x  <br /><br />Resolution power: 3.5&rdquo;<br /> Field of view: 1&deg;30&#39; (2.6 ft @ 100 ft)<br /> Minimum focusing distance: 2.46 ft (0.75 m)<br /> Stadia ratio: 1:100<br /> Stadia additive constant: +10 cm  <br /><br />Level Vial Sensitivity\r <ul>\r <li>Circular Level: 10&#39; / 2 mm</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Standard deviation\r <ul>\r <li>Per 1-km double-run leveling: &plusmn;1.5 mm</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Automatic Compensator\r <ul>\r <li>Type: wire-hung, magnetic damper<br />Compensation range: &plusmn;16&#39;<br />Setting accuracy: &plusmn;0.5"</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Horizontal Circle\r <ul>\r <li>Diameter of circle: 4.3 in (110 mm)<br />Minimum increment: 1&deg; / 1 g<br />Scale reading (direct): 1&deg; / 1 g<br />Reading by estimation: 0.1&deg; / 0.1</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Dimensions\r <ul>\r <li>Instrument(LxWxH): 7.5 x 5.0 x 4.8 in (190 x 128 x 123 mm)<br />Carrying case(LxWxH): 11.5 x 6.7 x 6.4 in (292 x 170 x 163 mm)</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Weight\r <ul>\r <li>Instrument: 2.8 lbs (1.25 kg)<br />Carrying case: 2.7 lbs (1.2 kg)</li>\r </ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081028195110', '20080919070322', '20090210174149', 'Topcon AT-G6', NULL, '<strong></strong> <br /><br /><strong>Surveying and Engineering Automatic Levels </strong> <br /><br />Topcon&#39;s engineering and construction automatic levels are streamlined and more compact than ever. They are lightweight for easy transport and the completely waterproof telescope is effective for all kinds of wet surveying operations.  <br /><br /><strong>Angular reading to 10 minutes (AT-G1) </strong><br />Model AT-G1 has a glass horizontal circle which is graduated in 10 minute divisions (10c divisions) and numbered every degree (one grade) with calibrations from 0&deg; to 360&deg; (0g to 400g). Furthermore, readings are possible through a 25x reading microscope, with only a slight shift of the eye, from the telescope eyepiece. The horizontal circle freely rotates for zero alignment.  <br /><br /><strong>Waterproof sealed telescope construction </strong><br />The instrument has a completely waterproof telescope and is therefore ideal for all kinds of wet-surveying operations, in light rain or in tunnels. Only test-approved telescopes are used and dry nitrogen gas is sealed in the telescope tube. This effectively prevents lens clouding and moisture condensation.  <br /><br /><strong>2 speed focusing (AT-G1) </strong><br />Fine and coarse focusing is provided by a coaxial focusing knob, which permits rapid setting and accurate focusing for perfect image at the same time. <br /><br /><strong>Clamp less fine horizontal adjustments </strong><br />Fine horizontal adjustments are possible at any point through 360&deg; (400g) of the arc, without clamping action. This means that target alignments are greatly speeded up. Furthermore, fine horizontal knobs are available on both sides for very easy and speedy adjustments.  <br /><br />Very short 0.5 meter focusing (AT-G3/G4/G7N) <br />AT-G3/G4/G7N have a short range setting position of 0.5 meter that is especially suitable for close range work carried out by builders and contractors.  <br /><br /><strong>Rapid, stable automatic leveling </strong><br />A time-proven magnetically damped compensator is incorporated for automatic leveling action. It is not affected by fine vibrations and has been proven to have very stable precision, thus speeding up automatic leveling operations and producing accurate results. The Topcon-exclusive automatic leveling system utilizes four special mylar ribbons for hanging the magnetic damper compensator. The compensator is therefore not influenced by the magnetic field, as well as having superior resistance to cold, heat and shock. <br /><br /><strong>Rubber eyepiece cap </strong><br />Sighting through Topcon&#39;s AT-G7 is safe for anyone who wears eyeglasses. With their protective rubber eyepiece caps, scratches and abrasions are reduced or eliminated completely.', '20081028195110-AT-G2_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '3500000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<table border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">\r <tbody>\r <tr>\r <td style="background-image: url(http://www.alatsurvey.com/home/templates/digitaleye_mitra_blue/images/box/top.png); background-repeat: repeat-x;" height="664" valign="top">\r <table class="contentpaneopen" border="0">\r <tbody>\r <tr>\r <td colspan="2" valign="top"><br /><br /><strong>AT-G2 </strong> <br /><br /><strong>Telescope </strong> <br /><br />Length ( mm/in.) : 229/9  <br /><br />Image : erect  <br /><br />Magnification : 32x  <br /><br />Objective lens ( mm/in. ) : 45/1.8  <br /><br />Relative brightness : 1.98  <br /><br />Field of view : 1&deg;20&#39;  <br /><br />Resolving power :2.5&rdquo;  <br /><br />Minimum focus ( m/ft. ) :1.0/3.2  <br /><br />Stadia constant ( m ) :0  <br /><br />Stadia ratio :100    <br /><br /><strong>Circular level </strong> <br /><br />Sensitivity ( /2mm ): 8&#39;    <br /><br /><strong>Automatic leveling </strong> <br /><br />Setting accuracy : &plusmn;0.3&rdquo;  <br /><br />Compensating range : &plusmn;15&#39;    <br /><br /><strong>Accuracy 1km double run level </strong> <br /><br />Without optical micrometer ( mm ) : &plusmn;0.7  <br /><br />With optical micrometer ( mm ) : &plusmn;0.4    <br /><br /><strong>Horizontal circle </strong> <br /><br />Diameter ( mm/in. ): 117/4.7  <br /><br />Minimum division : 1&deg; ( 1 g )    <br /><br /><strong>Weight </strong> <br /><br />Instrument ( kgs./lbs. ) : 1.8/4.1  <br /><br />Plastic carrying case ( kgs./lbs. ) : 1.3/2.9    <br /><br />Designs and specifications herein are subject to change without notice.  <br /><br />Technical specifications for AT-G1, AT-G3, AT-G4, AT-G6, AT-G7N also available, please contact us for further information.</td>\r </tr>\r </tbody>\r </table>\r </td>\r <td width="4" height="664" valign="top" background="http://www.alatsurvey.com/home/templates/digitaleye_mitra_blue/images/box/right.png"><img src="http://www.alatsurvey.com/home/templates/digitaleye_mitra_blue/images/box/top_right.png" border="0" alt="" width="14" height="33" /></td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td width="5"><img src="http://www.alatsurvey.com/home/templates/digitaleye_mitra_blue/images/box/bot_left.png" border="0" alt="" width="12" height="12" /></td>\r <td background="http://www.alatsurvey.com/home/templates/digitaleye_mitra_blue/images/box/bot.png"><img src="http://www.alatsurvey.com/home/templates/digitaleye_mitra_blue/images/box/bot.png" border="0" alt="" width="2" height="12" /></td>\r </tr>\r </tbody>\r </table>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081028195631', '20080919070322', '20080919070021', 'Nikon AC-2S', NULL, 'The economical, compact and lightweight AC-2S features a built-in compensator with magnetic damper that automatically levels line of sight. With an endless horizontal tangent screw, it is operable with either hand and employs a friction brake for faster operation. Moreover, it can be mounted on flat- or spherical-head tripod.', '20081028195631-level_ac2s_150150x.gif', 1, 0, '5500000', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Telescope\r <ul>\r <li>Tube Length : 7.5 in (190 mm)<br />Image: erect<br />Effective diameter of objective: 1.2 in (30 mm)<br />Magnification: 24x<br />Resolution power: 3.5&rdquo;<br />Field of view: 1&deg;30&#39; (2.6 ft @ 100 ft)<br />Minimum focusing distance: 2.46 ft (0.75 m)<br />Stadia ratio: 1:100<br />Stadia additive constant: +10 cm</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Level Vial Sensitivity\r <ul>\r <li>Circular Level: 10&#39; / 2 mm</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Standard deviation\r <ul>\r <li>Per 1-km double-run leveling: &plusmn;1.5 mm</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Automatic Compensator\r <ul>\r <li>Type: wire-hung, magnetic damper<br />Compensation range: &plusmn;16&#39;<br />Setting accuracy: &plusmn;0.5"</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Horizontal Circle\r <ul>\r <li>Diameter of circle: 4.3 in (110 mm)<br />Minimum increment: 1&deg; / 1 g<br />Scale reading (direct): 1&deg; / 1 g<br />Reading by estimation: 0.1&deg; / 0.1</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Dimensions\r <ul>\r <li>Instrument(LxWxH): 7.5 x 5.0 x 4.8 in (190 x 128 x 123 mm)<br />Carrying case(LxWxH): 11.5 x 6.7 x 6.4 in (292 x 170 x 163 mm)</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Weight\r <ul>\r <li>Instrument: 2.8 lbs (1.25 kg)<br />Carrying case: 2.7 lbs (1.2 kg)</li>\r </ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081028201053', '20080919070322', '20090319134642', 'Horizon HZ2028', NULL, 'This automatic level is designed for general building applications through to precision levelling for surveying and engineering projects.<br />A bright erect image with exceptional clarity means that staff readings are taken easily, accurately and quickly.<br />Optical sight for fast alignment to the target object.<br />Three foot screw instrument levelling.<br />Bubble reading prism at eye level for convenient checking.<br />Robust metal housing for protection against damage.<br />Accuracy 1.5mm for 1km double run levelling.<br />Minimum focussing distance: 500mm. <br />Friction braked rotation.<br />Endless horizontal drive knobs each side.<br />Stadia hairs for distance measuring.<br />360 degree horizontal circle.<br />Fits on any standard 5/8" tripod, flat or domed head.<br />This new design has both magnetic damping and air damping, resulting in shorter setting time and better stability of the compensator.', '20081028201053-level_hz2028_150150x.gif', 1, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081028201915', '20080919070322', '20090319134642', 'Horizon Aluminum Tripod Quick Lock', NULL, '<span style="font-family: Tahoma; color: #333333;">Designed to give maximum stability for a wide range of instruments.<br />The component parts are die-cast metal, finished in scratchproof epoxy powder paint coating.<br />Quick lock leg clamps allow for quick and easy setup and the tripod.<br />5/8" instrument fixing screw.<br />Sturdy hook attachment for suspending plumbing accessories.<br />The machined heads are precision finished to accept all survey instruments, large and small.<br />Tripod height: 0.98m -1.65m<br />Complete with strap.</span>', '20081028201915-level_aluminumQuickLock_150x.gif', 0, 0, '900000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081101160105', '20080919070322', '20080919070021', 'Nikon DTM 362', NULL, 'In addition to the enhancement of functions inherited from their predecessors&mdash;the DTM-350 and DTM-330&mdash;the new models feature a large graphic LCD, ergonomic keyboard and improved software for superior operability. They also come with a remarkable long battery life of 16 hours, IPx6 waterproof construction and intelligent feature coding systems. A 10,000-record data memory with job manager is available as is an newly designed EDM that offers increased speed and range. Moreover, they incorporate Nikon&rsquo;s superb optics as well as powerful and practical on-board survey programs. And all features are housed in a light and compact design.', '20081101160105-dmt352_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '94500000', NULL, NULL, '&plusmn;(3+2ppm x D)mm distance measurement accuracy&nbsp;<br />Same distance accuracy for both Prisms and Reflector Sheet&nbsp;<br />Just 1.6 sec. measuring time with 1mm distance resolution&nbsp;<br />5-second angle measurement accuracy&nbsp;<br />Quick and convenient feature code input system&nbsp;<br />USR user defined keys set as &ldquo;ONE-TOUCH access&rdquo; keys to your preferred functions&nbsp;<br />User customizable feature code list&nbsp;<br />First, on-site setting change capability&nbsp;<br />Feet &amp; Inch input and display&nbsp;<br />A special version of the DTM-352 that allows operation at extremely low temperatures down to &ndash;30&deg;C is available.', 'Specifications:\r <br /><br />Telescope\r <ul>\r <li>Tube Length: 158mm/6.22 in.<br />Magnification: 33x (21x/41x with optional eyepieces)<br />Effective diameter of objective: 45mm/1.77 in. (EDM: 50mm/1.97 in.)<br />Field of view: 1&deg;20&rsquo;<br />Resolving power: 2.5&rdquo;<br />Minimum focusing distance: 1.3m/4.26 ft.</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Distance measurement<br />Range with Nikon specified prisms\r <ul>\r <li>Normal conditions: (ordinary haze, visibility approx. 20km / 12.5 miles)<br />With reflector sheet (5x5 cm): 5 to 100m (16.4 to 328 ft.)<br />With mini prism: 1,000m/3,280 ft.<br />With single prism: 2,000m/6,560 ft<br />With triple prism: 2,600m/8,530 ft.<br />Good conditions : (No haze, visibility of over 40km/25 miles)<br />With reflector sheet (5x5 cm): 5 to 100m (16.4 to 328 ft.)<br />With mini prism: 1,200m/3,930 ft.<br />With single prism: 2,300m/7.540 ft.<br />With triple prism: 3,000m/9,840 ft.<br />Accuracy (Prism/Precise mode):&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;( 3+2ppm x D)mm<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;( 3+3ppm x D)mm (&ndash; 20&deg;C untuk &ndash; 10&deg;C, + 40&deg;C untuk + 50&deg;C</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Measuring interval*1\r <ul>\r <li>Precise mode: 1.6 sec. (initial 1.6 sec.)<br />Normal mode: 1.0 sec. (initial 1.4 sec.)</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Least count\r <ul>\r <li>Precise mode: 1mm/0.002 ft.<br />Normal mode: 10mm/0.02 ft.<br />Ambient temperature range*2: &ndash;20&deg;C to 50&deg;C/&ndash;4&deg;F to +122&deg;F</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Atmospheric correction\r <ul>\r <li>Temperature range: : &ndash;40&deg;C to 60&deg;C/&ndash;40&deg;F to +140&deg;F<br />Barometric pressure: 400 to 999mmHg/533 to 1,332hPa/15.8 to 39.3 in.Hg<br />Prism offset: : &ndash;999 to 999</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Angle measurement\r <ul>\r <li>Reading system: Photoelectric detection by incremental encoder<br />Horizontal angle: Diametrical(DTM-352)<br />Vertical angle: single<br />Minimum increment (Degree, Gon, MIL6400): Degree:1/5/10&rdquo;, Gon: 0.2/1/2mgon, MIL6400: 0.005/0.02/0,05mil<br />DIN 18723 accuracy&nbsp; (horizontal and vertical): 5&rdquo;/1.5mgon</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Tilt sensor:\r <ul>\r <li>Type: Dual-axis(DTM-352)<br />Method: Liquid-electric detection<br />Compensation range: &plusmn;3&#39;<br />Setting accuracy: 1"</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Level vial\r <ul>\r <li>Plate level vial: 30"/2mm<br />Circular level vial: 10&#39;/2mm</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Optical plummet\r <ul>\r <li>Magnification: 3x<br />Focusing range: 0.5m/1.6 ft. to 8<br />Display: Graphic LCD (128 x 64 dot)<br />Both sides(DTM-352)<br />Point memory: 10,000 records<br />Dimensions (W x D x H): 168 x 173 x 335mm/6.6 x 6.8 x 13.2 in.</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />Weight (approx.):\r <ul>\r <li>Main unit (with battery): 5.3kg/11.7 lbs.(DTM-352)<br />Battery: 0.4kg/0.9 lbs<br />Carrying case: 2.4kg/5.3 lbs</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br />On-board Ni-MH battery BC-65<br />Operation time\r <ul>\r <li>Continuous distance/angle measurement: Approx. 16 hours*3<br />Distance/angle measurement every 30 seconds: Approx. 27 hours<br />Angle measurement: Approx. 27 hours<br />Quick charger Q-75U/E: Approx. 2.0 hours for full recharge<br />Quick charger Q-70C (12V DC cigarette lighter charger): Approx. 2.0 hours (fully discharged BC-65 requires more than one charge)</li>\r </ul>', NULL, 'Nikon DMT352 ', 'nikon, dumartec, alat survey, alat navigasi', 'In addition to the enhancement of functions inherited from their predecessorsthe DTM-350 and DTM-330the new models feature a large graphic LCD, ergonomic keyboard and improved software for superior operability. '),
('20081101173432', '20080919070322', '20080919070021', 'Nikon NE202', NULL, NULL, '20081101173432-ne202_150150x.gif', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, 'The Nikon NE-202 theodolites feature a large, backlit LCD graphic display and keypad on both sides. Either screen can display both vertical and horizontal angles simultaneously.\r <br /><br />One-touch keys for common functions<br />Four one-touch keys make the NE-202 easy to use. Common functions are simple to perform&mdash;you can instantly convert vertical angles to percent of grade, reset the horizontal angle to zero, lock the horizontal angle displayed on the LCD while you reposition, or repeat a measurement. Operation is simple and efficient.\r <br /><br />Rugged and waterproof<br />With Nikon theodolites, you can count on reliable performance in tough conditions. Our theodolites are both rugged and waterproof. They have an IPX6 rating, meaning they can withstand powerful jets of water with no harmful effects.\r <br /><br />Extra light for dark conditions<br />Our theodolites feature built-in reticle illuminators that provide a clear view of the crosshairs to help you work in tunnels, mines or other environments with little or no light. The LCD graphic displays are backlit as well, so you can read them easily even in the darkest conditions.\r <br /><br />Focus to 2.3 ft.<br />The NE-202 feature a 30x telescope with a 45-mm objective aperture diameter. And Nikon&#39;s unique linear focusing mechanism improves focusing at both short and long distances. The minimum focusing distance is 2.3 ft. (0.7 m), so you can see sharp images even in confined spaces.\r <br /><br />Power management feature<br />The NE-202 can work for one hour more on either battery. You can extend battery life by setting the instrument to automatically shut off after 10 or 30 minutes of inactivity. And the power save function retains the last horizontal angle on display, so you can get right back to work.\r <br /><br />Built-in vertical compensation<br />The built-in vertical compensation ,automatically compensate to ensure precise vertical angle readings. The NE-202 have an accuracy of 5".', 'Telescope<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Effective diameter of objective: 1.77 in (45 mm)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Magnification : 30x<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Image: Erect<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Field of view:1&deg;20&#39; (2.3ft @ 100 ft / 2.3m @ 100 m)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum focusing distance: 2.3 ft ( 0.7 m )<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Stadia multiplier constant: 100<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Stadia additive constant: 0<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Reticle illuminator: provided<br /><br />Angle Measurement<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Reading system: photoelectric incremental encoder<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Circle diameter: 3.1 in (79 mm)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Unit of reading: degree / gon / mil<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Minimum digital reading&sup1; :5/10&rdquo;, &frac12; mgon, 0.02/0.05 mil<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Accuracy (DIN 18723) : 5&rdquo; /1 mgon<br /><br />Display / Keypad<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Front<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type: dot-matrix LCD ( 20 characters x 2 lines)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Backlight: 1-level illumination<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Keypad: 5 buttons<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Rear<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Type: dot-matrix LCD (20 characters x 2 lines)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Backlight: 1-level illumination<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Keypad: 5 buttons<br /><br />Optical Plummet<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Magnification: 3x<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Field of view: 5&deg;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Focus range: 1.6 ft(0.5 m) to infinity<br /><br />Level Sensitivity<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Plate Level: 30&rdquo; / 2 mm<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Circular level: 10&rsquo; / 2 mm<br /><br />Leveling Base<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Type: detachable<br /><br />Ambient temperature range: -4 TO 122 &deg;F (-20 to 50 C)<br /><br />Dimensions<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Instrument: 6.0 x 6.8 x 13.1 in (153.5 x 172 x 334 mm)<br /><br />Weight<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Instrument: 9.9 lbs (4.5 kg)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Carrying case: 8.6 lbs ( 3.9 kg)<br /><br />Power Supply<br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; * Battery type: 1.5V manganese AA (R6) x 6 or alkaline L40 (R6)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Continuous operating time ( at 68 &deg;F / 20C)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With manganese batteries: 22 hrs<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; With alkaline batteries: 48 hrs<br /><br />Notes<br />&sup1;1/5", 0.5/1 mgon, 0.005/0.02 mil available as an option.<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081101174218', '20080919070322', '20080919070021', 'Nikon NE101', NULL, NULL, '20081101174218-ne101_150150x.gif', 1, 0, '25000000', NULL, NULL, '<div class="mosimage_caption">NE101</div>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />One-touch keys for common functions<br />NE-101 theodolites feature five easy-to-use, one-touch keys: four to perform all common functions and a fifth to control the backlit LCD display and reticle illumination. You can instantly convert vertical angles to percent of grade, reset the horizontal angle to zero and lock the horizontal angle displayed on the LCD while you reposition or repeat a measurement.  <br /><br />Extra light for dark conditions<br />NE-101 theodolites feature a built-in reticle illuminator and backlit LCD display that allow you to work inside buildings as well as in tunnels, mines and other environments with little or no light. These features also come in handy during low-light conditions outdoors, such as near dawn or dusk.  <br /><br />Works longer on standard AA batteries<br />Unlike other instruments that require specialized batteries, NE-101 theodolites use six standard AA alkaline batteries. What&#39;s more, those batteries can power the NE-101 models for about 48 hours. A three-level bar graph on the LCD screen displays remaining battery power.  <br /><br />Rugged, all-weather reliability<br />With the NE-101 models, you can count on reliable performance in tough conditions. Nikon theodolites are lightweight, rugged and come with an IP54 rating. That means water can splash on them from any direction with no harmful effects.', '<ul>\r <li>Effective diameter of objective: 1.77 in (45 mm)<br />Magnification : 30x<br />Image: Erect<br />Field of view:1&deg;20&#39; (2.3ft @ 100 ft / 2.3m @ 100 m)<br />Minimum focusing distance: 2.3 ft ( 0.7 m )<br />Stadia multiplier constant: 100<br />Stadia additive constant: 0<br />Reticle illuminator: provided</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Angle Measurement\r <ul>\r <li>Reading system: photoelectric incremental encoder<br />Circle diameter: 3.1 in (79 mm)<br />Unit of reading: degree / gon / mil<br />Minimum digital reading&sup1; :5/10&rdquo;, &frac12; mgon, 0.02/0.05 mil<br />Accuracy (DIN 18723) : 7&rdquo; /2 mgon</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Display / Keypad\r <ul>\r <li>Front<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Type: dot-matrix LCD ( 20 characters x 2 lines)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Backlight: 1-level illumination<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;Keypad: 5 buttons</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Optical Plummet\r <ul>\r <li>Magnification: 2.2x<br />Field of view: 5&deg;<br />Focus range: 4.3 ft(1.3 m) fixed</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Level Sensitivity\r <ul>\r <li>Plate Level: 40&rdquo; / 2 mm<br />Circular level: 10&rsquo; / 2 mm</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Leveling Base\r <ul>\r <li>Type: detachable</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Ambient temperature range: -4 TO 122 &deg;F (-20 to 50 C)  <br /><br />Dimensions\r <ul>\r <li>Instrument: 6.0 x 6.8 x 13.1 in (153.5 x 172 x 334 mm)</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Weight\r <ul>\r <li>Instrument: 9.8 lbs (4.5 kg)<br />Carrying case: 5.4 lbs ( 2.5 kg)</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Power Supply\r <ul>\r <li>Battery type: 1.5V alkaline AA x 6<br />&nbsp;Continuous operating time ( at 68 &deg;F / 20C)<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;With alkaline batteries: 48 hrs<br />Notes<br />&sup1;1/5", 0.5/1 mgon, 0.005/0.02 mil available as an option.</li>\r </ul>', NULL, 'Nikon NE101 ', 'nikon, garmin, garmin indonesia', 'One-touch keys for common functions NE-101 theodolites feature five easy-to-use, one-touch keys: four to perform all common functions and a fifth to control the backlit LCD display and reticle illumination.'),
('20081103200111', '20080919070322', '20081101155021', 'GPS Magelan / Thales Promark3', NULL, '<span style="font-size: x-small;">Continuing the Magellan (formerly Thales) GPS Advantage<br /> ProMark&trade;3 continues the Magellan GPS tradition as the next generation of easy-to-use, turnkey survey systems. All the required hardware and software needed to perform fast centimeter accurate static, stop &amp; go, and kinematic surveys, as well as GIS/mapping, is ready to go, right out of the box.</span>', '20081103200324-GPS MAGELLANx.jpg', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<span style="font-size: x-small;"><br /> ProMark3 easily beats optical instruments in terms of portability and range. It is highly shock and water resistant, designed to perform even in the toughest environments. Easy-to-learn, easy-to-use and cost-effective, ProMark3 is the must-have GPS system for post-processed survey.<br /> More Accurate and 33% Faster<br /> ProMark3 delivers centimeter, post-processed positioning for accurate surveys as well as sub-meter accuracy in real-time for GIS/mapping and navigation.<br /> Magellan Prism&trade; technology reduces survey data collection time by as much as 33% for a marked increase in productivity. Prism technology gets surveyors onto the next job faster than ever and also allows GPS survey under poor satellite tracking conditions. This saves time both marking points and acquiring satellites enabling you to perform more efficient surveys and get jobs done quickly.*<br /> Enjoy the Renown ProMark Ease-of-use<br /> ProMark3 offers a user-friendly interface that capitalizes on the acclaimed ease-of-use of ProMark2 and MobileMapper&trade; to bring simplicity to every survey operation. The simple interface, intuitive software, large color touch screen and full alphanumeric keypad make deployment a snap.<br /> Survey data processing is also made easy with GNSS Solutions&trade; office software. GNSS Solutions is a comprehensive package that provides all the tools required to successfully process GPS, GLONASS and SBAS survey data. GNSS Solutions includes advanced blunder detection and quality analysis tools to ensure accurate and reliable output. The simple Wizard guides you through planning, processing, quality control, reporting, data exporting and more.<br /> Reliability and Flexibility Surveyors Need<br /> Rugged and lightweight, ProMark3 offers maximum portability to virtually any job site. It enables larger surveys to be performed by a one-man crew with minimal moves and less operational downtime. Embedded monitoring, diagnostics and quality-control tools help make certain the job is done correctly while still in the field, further ensuring that no time is wasted.<br /> ProMark3&#39;s water resistant design and long-life rechargeable battery makes operation safe and easy . USB, Bluetooth&reg; wireless technology and SD-card compatibility offer easy communication and unlimited expandability.<br /> Available in 9 languages, the user interface can easily be localized for your region.<br /> Expand your Service Offer with GIS<br /> ProMark3 offers the value of a complete professional GIS/Mapping system at no additional cost. Powerful yet easy-to-use mapping features include point, line and area mapping, real-time area calculation, offset measurement and data nesting.<br /> MobileMapper Office software links the ProMark3 receiver to the GIS database. Simply upload shape files and other GIS data to be updated in the field. Editing data and exporting .SHP, .MIF, .DXF and .CSV files is easy. Upload basemaps and vector background maps to the free memory or to an SD card. MobileMapper Office includes raster image support so you can use geo-referenced images or create your own background images to provide custom reference points.<br /> *Performance values assume minimum of 5 satellites, following the procedures recommended in the product manual. High-multipath areas, high PDOP values and periods of severe atmospheric conditions may degrade performance.</span>', NULL, NULL, 'Garmin Indonesia', 'Garmin, magellan', NULL),
('20081205181623', '20081020144912', '20081101155021', 'Aldis Lamp CXD-120', NULL, 'In accordance with MSC.95(72); Applied to signal communication between two vessels, and between vessel and shore.\r \r  \r \r Type           : CXD-120\r \r Battery       : Lithium Battery DC-24V\r \r Bulb           : 24V-60W ', '20081205181623-aldis-lamp-CXD-120x.jpg', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081103202432', '20080919070322', '20081103201619', 'Suunto KB-14', NULL, NULL, '20081103202432-Suunto-KB-14x.gif', 0, 0, '1250000', NULL, NULL, '<div class="mosimage_caption">KB-14</div>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />The KB-14 hand-bearing compass is an excellent tool for foresters, surveyors and geologist and many others. Suunto bearing compasses are designed to combie extreme accuracy with ease and speed of operation. With a built-in, maintenance-free ligh sourve the compasses can be used even in total darkness.  <br /><br />KB-14 Story <br />&nbsp; <br />Suunto bearing compasses are designed to combine extreme accuracy is 1/3&deg;, graduation 1/2&deg; and the compass weighs only 115 g. The flat, compact housing has no protruding or adjustable parts and are designed to stand up to heavy-duty wear. The compasses are water resistant. <br />The cards of these compasses are immersed in a special dampening fluid that ensures vibrationless, smooth movement. They are povited on polished sapphire tips. The veering assembly is to all intents and purposes subject ton o wear and the liquied remains clear and its viscosity low under all conditions.  <br /><br />The compasses have been given permanent anti-static teratment. The lens apertures of the KB-14 and KB-20 types are restricted horizontally by a column, which automatically centers the eye on the optical axis, thus elimination parallax.  <br /><br />KB-14 compasses are also available with efficient lithium battery powered illumination. There is also a rubber cover accessory for all the KB-14 versions that is made of a saltwater and UV-resistant mixture of EPDM and natural rubber.', '<ul>\r <li>KB-14/360 also available in versions KB-14/360 B (battery), KB-14/360 R (reverse scale), KB-14/360 RB (reverse scale, battery), KB-14/360 Q (gon), KB-14/360 QD (gon, declination correction), KB-14/360-6400, KB-14/360 D (declination correction), KB-14/360-6400 D (declination correction) <br />KB-14/6000:          \r <ul>\r <li>Scale : 0-6000 mils, interval10.xx <br />Housing: anolized light-alloy, optical adjustment, optical adjustment for reading, battery powered illumination as an accessory </li>\r </ul>\r </li>\r <li>KB-14/400D:&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Scale : 0-400 gons&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Interval : 0,5&deg;&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; Housing : anolized light-alloy, optical adjustment, declination correction, optical adjustment for reading</li>\r </ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081104153618', '20080919070322', '20081103201619', 'Suunto KB-20', NULL, 'The Suunto KB-20 is a hand-bearing floating compass weights only 40 g. It is an ideal instrument for marine, professional and outdoor use. The Suunto KB-20 has an accuracy that is better than 1 degree, graduation is 1&deg; and has reverse scale.  <br /><br />Features:&nbsp;\r <ul>\r <li>Scale : 0 - 360&deg; gons&nbsp;<br />Interval : 1 &deg;&nbsp;<br />Housing : optical adjustment, optical adjustment for reading</li>\r </ul>', '20081104153618-kb20_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '700000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081104155347', '20080919070322', '20081103201619', 'Tandem', NULL, 'he Suunto Tandem is a liquid-filled precision compass and clinometer in one compact aluminum housing. This instrument is an excellent tool for surveyors, engineers, cartographers, geologists, miners, architects and for anyone who needs to be able to measure directional indications, heights, vertical angles and slopes - with speed and accuracy.  <br /><br />Tandem Story <br />&nbsp; <br />The Suunto Tandem also features a lanyard, and a convenient carrying pouch with a belt loop. You can change the Tandem from compass to clinometer with the click of your wrist.<br />', '20081104155347-tandem_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '2100000', NULL, NULL, 'Features:&nbsp;\r <ul>\r <li>High accuracy - precise readings in seconds&nbsp;<br />Durable aluminum housing - protects against impact, corrosion and water&nbsp;<br />Edges at 90 degrees angles for contact measuring&nbsp;<br />Individually calibrated&nbsp;<br />Optical adjustment for reading&nbsp;<br />Same quality capsules as in the regular PMS and KBS&nbsp;<br />Tandem 360 PC / 360 R&nbsp;    \r <ul>\r <li>Scales : 0 &plusmn; 90 &deg;, 0 &plusmn; 150 %&nbsp;<br />Converstion table : cosines 0 - 50 gon</li>\r </ul>\r </li>\r </ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081104162619', '20080919070322', '20081103201619', 'Suunto PM5', NULL, 'Suunto PM-5 provides you with a large selection of height meters, clinometers and combined height- and clinometers.  <br /><br />Suunto height meters are instruments for measuring the heights, especially the height of trees, with great accuracy and speed. The height meters can also be used to determine the angle of a gradient.  <br /><br />Suunto hand-held clinometers are precision instruments used all over the world by surveyors, engineers, cartographers, geologists, miners and architects and many others to measure heights, vertical angles and slopes quickly and easily.  <br /><br />PM 5 Story&nbsp; <br />&nbsp; <br />Both height meters and clinometers have sturdy housing bodies made from corrosion resistant anodized aluminum alloy. The scale cards run on special bearings in hermetically sealed plastic containers filled with a liquid which guarantees that they run smoothly and stop quickly.  <br /><br />The liquid will not freeze or evaporate, retains full damping properties in all working conditions and eliminates irritating scale vibrations.  <br /><br />There is a large selection of scales to choose from. These include normal linear angle scales, i.e. degrees, gons and mils as well as per cent scales, topographic scales, metric or American and special secant scales.', '20081104162619-pm5_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '1400000', NULL, NULL, 'Features:&nbsp;\r <ul>\r <li>Height meter    \r <ul>\r <li>PM-5/1520 P: Scales: 15 m and 20 m, conversion table 20 m - degrees, optical adjustment for reading, battery powered illumination as an optional accessory&nbsp;</li>\r </ul>\r </li>\r <li>Clinometers    \r <ul>\r <li>PM-5/360 PC : Scales: 0 &plusmn; 90&deg;, 0 &plusmn; 150 %, conversion table : cosines 0-45 &deg;, optical adjustment for reading, battery-powered illumination as an accessory&nbsp;<br />PM-5/360 S: Scales: 0 &plusmn; 90&deg;, secant, conversion table: cosines 0-45 &deg;, optical adjustment for reading, battery-powered illumination as an accessory&nbsp;<br />&nbsp;PM-5/360 PCB: Scales: 0 &plusmn; 90&deg;, 0 &plusmn; 150 %, conversion table: cosines 0-45 &deg;, optical adjustment for reading, standard battery-powered illumination&nbsp;<br />PM-5/400 PC: Scales: 0 &plusmn; 100 gons, 0 &plusmn; 150 %, conversion table 0-50 gons, optical adjustment for reading, battery-powered illumination as an accessory&nbsp;<br />PM-5/6400: Scales: 0 &plusmn; 150 %, 0 &plusmn; 1600 mils, optical adjustment for reading, battery-powered illumination as an accessory&nbsp;<br />PM-5/SPC: Scales: 0 &plusmn; 150 %, secant, conversion table: % - degrees, optical adjustment for reading, battery-powered illumination as an accessory&nbsp;</li>\r </ul>\r </li>\r <li>Combined height and clinometers    \r <ul>\r <li>PM-5/1520 PC: Scales: 0 &plusmn; 150 %, 15 m and 20 m, conversion table 20 m - degrees, optical adjustment for reading, battery powered illumination as an optional accessory<br />PM-5/1520 D: Scales: 0 &plusmn; 90 %, 15 m and 20 m, cosines 0 - 45&deg;, optical adjustment for reading, battery powered illumination as an optional accessory </li>\r </ul>\r </li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Suunto clinometers and height meters are also available in feet scales for the US . market.', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
