('20081117161645', '20080919070322', '20081103201619', 'MCB', NULL, '<div class="mosimage_caption">MCB</div>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><span class="normal">An ergonomically designed multi-purpose mirror compass that combines precision with practicality.</span> <br /><br /><strong><span class="header">Accurate and Reliable Mirror Compasses</span></strong><br /><br /><span class="normal">The MC range of mirror compasses provides an invaluable tool for those who place a particular premium on accurate and reliable directional measurements; for example surveyors, miners, architects, rescue patrols, hikers, boaters and the military. The declination adjustment system, standard throughout the range, is especially useful when working in areas of large magnetic variation, while the sighting notch provides superior accuracy.</span> <br /><br /><strong><span class="ode">Product Features</span></strong> <br /><br /><span class="ode"> <span class="normal">\r <li>Two Zone System</li>\r <li>fixed declination correction scale</li>\r <li>jewel bearing</li>\r <li> floating</li>\r <li>detachable snap-lock lanyard with whistle</li>\r <li>sighting hole and notch for accurate bearings</li>\r <li>size: 58 x 68 x 18 mm / 2.3" x 2.7" x 0.7"(with lid closed)</li>\r <li>weight: 36 g / 1.3 oz</li>\r </span></span>', '20081117161645-MCB_150x.jpg', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081117163725', '20080919070322', '20081103201619', 'MCA', NULL, '<div class="mosimage_caption">MCA</div>\r <br /><br /><span class="normal">A compact mirror compass designed with practicality in mind.</span>\r <br /><br /><strong><span class="header">Accurate and Reliable Mirror Compasses</span></strong><br /><br /><span class="normal">The MC range of mirror compasses provides an invaluable tool for those who place a particular premium on accurate and reliable directional measurements; for example surveyors, miners, architects, rescue patrols, hikers, boaters and the military. The declination adjustment system, standard throughout the range, is especially useful when working in areas of large magnetic variation, while the sighting notch provides superior accuracy.</span>\r <br /><br /><span class="ode"><strong>Product Features</strong><br /><br /></span> <span class="normal">\r <li>Two Zone System</li>\r <li>fixed declination correction</li>\r <li>jewel bearing</li>\r <li>sighting notch</li>\r <li>cm or inch scales</li>\r <li>detachable snap lock lanyard</li>\r <li>mirror lid locks open at various angles (60&ordm;, 120&ordm;, 180&ordm;)</li>\r <li>size: 56 x 84 x 15 mm / 2.2" x 3.3"  x 0.6" (with the lid closed)</li>\r <li>weight: 42 g / 1.5 oz</li>\r </span>', '20081117163725-mca-d_150x.jpg', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081117170527', '20080919070322', '20081103201619', 'A-40', NULL, '<div class="mosimage_caption">A-40</div>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><span class="normal">A compact and durable high-accuracy compass with luminous bezel and markings. The integrated curvimeter together with centimeter, inch and conversion scales make it ideal for the demanding navigator.</span> <br /><br /><strong><span class="header">User Friendly Recreational Compasses</span></strong><br /><br /><span class="normal">The A-Range of recreational compasses is a series of handy, well designed, navigational aids which are assets in any environment. All four models in the series (A-10, A-20, A-30L and A-40) are compact, high-accuracy instruments made from durable, clear, scratch resistant acrylic that have been ergonomically designed to fit into the palm of your hand for optimum ease of use. These light-weight compasses feature a fixed declination correction scale as well as a patent-pending lanyard snap-lock enabling the compass to be easily detached from the lanyard.</span> <br /><br /><span class="ode"><strong>Product Features</strong><br /><br /></span> <span class="normal">\r <li> Two Zone System</li>\r <li> fixed declination correction scale</li>\r <li> detachable snap lock lanyard</li>\r <li> jewel bearing</li>\r <li>integrated curvimeter (map measurer), conversion scales</li>\r <li>baseplate with magnifying lens</li>\r <li>luminous bezel and markings</li>\r <li>control marking holes </li>\r <li>cm or inch scales</li>\r <li>size: 57 x 120 mm / 2.2" x 4.2" </li>\r <li>weight: 38 g / 1.3 oz</li>\r </span>', '20081117170527-A-40_150x.jpg', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081117190321', '20080919070258', '20081117190155', 'Furuno Radar 1623', NULL, 'Small in size, the 1623 is big on power, clarity and advanced radar features. The slim-line monochrome LCD display and lightweight radome antenna make it ideal for power or sail boats as small as 17 feet.  <br /><br />This 2.2kW radar has a 16 nautical mile range, yet will zoom down to 1/8 nautical mile for tight navigation in harbors and inlets. The 1623 radar lets you readily identify objects, thanks to a high definition 6" Silver Bright LCD screen that clearly separates targets. Plus, the four-tone target display lets you easily differentiate between stronger and weaker echoes, helping to alert you of any danger.  <br /><br />Standard Features :\r <ul>\r <li>Waterproof, 6 Inch Silver Bright Monochrome LCD Display </li>\r <li>13 User Selectable Range Scales from 1/8 to 16 N.M. </li>\r <li>Ergonomic design with predictable menu </li>\r <li>Display Resolution of 240(H) X 320(V) Dots </li>\r <li>Targets Displayed in up to 4 Levels of Gray Tones </li>\r <li>2.2 Kilowatt Transmitter Unit </li>\r <li>New Tri-speed 15" radome antenna, increases RPM at short ranges for better target accuracy </li>\r <li>3 Transmitter Pulse lengths and Repetition Rates </li>\r <li>Linear Receiver with 10 dB Noise Figure </li>\r <li>Automatic Receiver Tuning </li>\r <li>Automatic or Manual Sea-Clutter (STC) Adjustment </li>\r <li>Automatic or Manual Receiver Gain Adjustment </li>\r <li>Sector Blanking </li>\r <li>Rain Clutter (FTC) Control </li>\r <li>Echo Stretch and Interference Rejection Modes </li>\r <li>Watchman Mode to control the Radar system for Vessel Safety </li>\r <li>Reverse Video Display (White Targets and Marks on a Black Background) </li>\r <li>Full Screen Navigation Data Display in the Standby Mode* </li>\r <li>Omni Pad Control for rapid Cursor and Menu Operation </li>\r <li>Picture Off-Center Shift </li>\r <li>Electronic Bearing Line and Variable Range Marker </li>\r <li>Target or Echo Trails with Selectable Time Intervals </li>\r <li>Waypoint Lollipop On-Screen to aid in Vessel Navigation* </li>\r <li>Adjustable Duplex (In or Out) Radar Guard Zone Alarm </li>\r <li>TLL (Target Lat/Lon) output for use with plotter (must accept TLL sentence info)* </li>\r <li>Time offset adjustment </li>\r <li>[PROG] key provides menu shortcuts </li>\r <li>User programmable Nav Data Screens </li>\r <li>Ability to connect BBWGPS GPS/WAAS receiver </li>\r <li>Wind indication with appropriate sensor input</li>\r </ul>', '20081117190321-furuno1623_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '21250000', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Specifications:\r <ul>\r <li>Display 6" Mono LCD</li>\r <li>Antenna 15" Radome </li>\r <li>Range 16 n.m.&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Power Output 2.2 kW </li>\r <li>Horizontal Beamwidth 6.2 degrees</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <br />Shipping Information:\r <ul>\r <li>24 lbs., 1 Carton&nbsp;</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><span style="color: #000000;"> <br /><br /><br />Power Requirements:        \r <ul>\r <li>12 or 24 VDC Only, 36 Watts </li>\r <li>Approximately 8 Watts, in Standby/Watchman Mode </li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br />Notes:<br />* Appropriate Nav Data Input Required </span>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081117195758', '20080919070258', '20081117190155', 'Furuno Radar 1715', NULL, '<div class="mosimage_caption">Radar 1715</div>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">The MODEL 1715 is a high contrast LCD radar designed for pleasure craft and small fishing boats. Radar echoes are presented in four shades of gray on the 7" Silver Bright LCD. The Radar offers detailed pictures of coastline and targets at short ranges thanks to narrower pulselengths and dual IF bandwidths. The antenna rotation speed automatically changes depending on the range selection for optimum target detection. The compact, waterproof display allows table top or panel mounting in the cockpit or on the open fly bridge. </span> <br /><br /><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">The radar has a power saving Watchman mode. In this mode, the antenna is stopped and the transmission is off, while the screen displays nav data only. The radar wakes up at a specified time interval (5, 10 or 20 min) and operates for a minute. If a target enters the Guard Zone, an audible alarm sounds and the radar goes into its normal operating mode, cancelling the Watchman mode. The alarm may also be set to work for a target leaving the Zone. </span> <br /><br /><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Other standard features include: EBL (Electronic Bearing Line), VRM (Variable Range Marker), TLL output (Target L/L), Cursor L/L readout, Echo Trail, Guard Zone Alarm, Anti Clutter Rain, Automatic control of tuning and sensitivity. The A/C RAIN control improves the target detection in the rain by elaborate design of the receiver. </span> <br /><br /><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">With use of nav data inputs in NMEA 0183 format, the radar offers additional functions. Graphical and numeric waypoint information can be shown on the display. The Waypoint is indicated by a lollipop mark for easy identification on the radar display. In the TLL output function, you can use the cursor to output a specified target&#39;s L/L to the optional GPS navigator as a mark.</span> <br /><br /><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Standard Features:&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>\r <ul>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">High Contrast 7" Silver Bright LCD for excellent sunlight viewability&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">14 range scales from 0.125 to 24 nm&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Low power consumption in Watchman mode - only 8 W&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Dual bandwidth IF amplifier: broad band for high fidelity in short ranges, narrow band for enhanced detection in long ranges&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Variable antenna speeds with range scales for optimum performance on all ranges&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Cursor position can be read in L/L (GPS Navigator is required)&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Waypoint Lollipop On-Screen to aid in Vessel Navigation (GPS Navigator is required)&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Programmable Navigation Data repeater feature&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Zoom in to a specific area&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Reverse video feature for effective use at night&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Guard Zone Alarm ( US Patent No.5032842)</span></li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;"> </span>', '20081117195758-furuno1715_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '25000000', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Specifications:\r <ul>\r <li>Display 7 " Mono LCD&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Antenna 18" Radome&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Range 24 n.m.&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Power Output&nbsp; 2.2 kW&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Horizontal Beamwidth&nbsp; 5.2 degrees</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Shipping Information:\r <ul>\r <li>29 lbs, 1 Carton 13"x 21"x 28"&nbsp;</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />&nbsp;Power Requirements:\r <ul>\r <li>12 to 24 VDC, 38 W (max), 8 W (in Watchman mode) </li>\r <li>115/230 VAC with optional rectifier PR-62 </li>\r </ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081118131539', '20080919070258', '20081117190155', 'Furuno Radar 1823', NULL, '<span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Engineered for 30&#39;- 65&#39; boats, the Furuno 1832 radar offers exceptional power, target detection and reliability. Featuring Furuno&#39;s custom microwave IC receiver design, this radar has a 10" diagonal CRT daylight-bright display with eight-level quantization. Plus, it&#39;s packed with high-speed micro-processor technology and features that help you identify what&#39;s out there. And like other Furuno radars, it can be inter-connected with other nav equipment, chart plotters and even sounders, through Furuno&#39;s programmable NMEA 0183 interface system. The 1832 comes with a sleek 24" radome antenna.</span> <br /><br /><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Standard Features:&nbsp;&nbsp;</span>\r <ul>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">High Resolution, Non-Glare 10 Inch Monochrome CRT Display&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">4.0 Kilowatt Transmitter Unit&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Up to 15 User Selected Range Scales from 1/8 to 36N.M.&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">User Adjustable Duplex (In or Out) Radar (Guard Zone) Alarm&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">User Selected Time Echo Trails for Target Threat Assessment&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Automatic or Manual Tuning Receiver&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">9db Noise Factor Logarithmic Receiver&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Three Modulator Pulse lengths and Repetition Rates&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-family: Arial; color: #333333;">Programmable F1 and F2 Keys for Optimized Radar Picture&nbsp;</span></li>\r <li><span style="font-