 or Watchman Mode</li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br />Notes <br />*&nbsp;&nbsp; Appropriate Nav Data Input Required. <br />** Appropriate Compass and Nav Data Input, Required. </span>', '20081118131539-furuno1832_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '34800000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081118132559', '20080919070258', '20081117190155', 'Furuno Radar 1932', NULL, 'Engineered for 30&#39;- 65&#39; boats, the Furuno 1932MK2 radar offers exceptional power, target detection and reliability. Featuring Furuno&#39;s custom microwave IC receiver design, this radar has a 10" diagonal CRT daylight-bright display with eight-level quantization. Plus, it&#39;s packed with high-speed micro-processor technology and features that help you identify what&#39;s out there. And like other Furuno radars, it can be inter-connected with other nav equipment, chart plotters and even sounders, through Furuno&#39;s programmable NMEA 0183 interface system. The 1932MK2 comes with a 3.5&#39; open array antenna.  <br /><br />Standard Features:&nbsp;\r <ul>\r <li>High Resolution, Non-Glare 10 Inch CRT Display </li>\r <li>4.0 Kilowatt Transmitter Unit </li>\r <li>Up to 16 User Selected Range Scales from 1/8th to 48N.M. </li>\r <li>User Adjustable Duplex (In or Out) Radar (Guard Zone) Alarm </li>\r <li>User Selected Time of Echo Trails for Target Threat Assessment </li>\r <li>Automatic or Manual Tuning Receiver </li>\r <li>6db Noise Factor Logarithmic Receiver </li>\r <li>Three Modulator Pulse lengths and Repetition Rates </li>\r <li>Programmable F1 and F2 Keys for Optimized Radar Picture </li>\r <li>Automatic or Manual Control of Rain Clutter (FTC) </li>\r <li>Automatic or Manual Control of Sea Clutter (STC) </li>\r <li>Waypoint Lollipop Navigation Aid Overlaid on Radar Picture * </li>\r <li>Power Saving Watchman, or Sleep Mode for Safety at Anchor </li>\r <li>Multi-step Interference Rejecter and Echo Stretch to Enhance Picture </li>\r <li>100% Picture Off-Centering or 2 x Target Area Zoom </li>\r <li>Two VRM&#39;s and EBL&#39;s for Rapid Target Data, one may be Offset </li>\r <li>Course-up, Head-up, North-up or True Motion Display Modes ** </li>\r <li>Navigation Data Display in Standby * </li>\r <li>Automatic Video Level Adjustment (up to 8 Levels) </li>\r <li>Target/Cursor Position and Output to Plotter, using TLL Key * </li>\r <li>Optional ARP10, 10 Target ARPA **</li>\r </ul>', '20081118132559-furuno1932_150150x.gif', 0, 0, '57750000', NULL, NULL, NULL, '<ul>\r <li>Display 10" Mono CRT&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Antenna 3.5&#39; Open Array&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Range 48 n.m.&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Power Output&nbsp; 4 kW&nbsp; </li>\r <li>Horizontal Beamwidth&nbsp; 2.4 degrees&nbsp; </li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Shipping Information:\r <ul>\r <li>102 lbs., 4 Carton </li>\r </ul>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Power Requirements:\r <ul>\r <li>12 or 24/32 VDC, 52 Watts, Fuse Change Required </li>\r <li>28 Watts in Power Economy, Standby or Watchman Mode </li>\r </ul>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081118134404', '20080919070258', '20081117190155', 'Furuno GP32', NULL, 'he Furuno GP32 GPS receiver is a high performance, compact navigator for boaters who want quality and reliability without all the "bells and whistles" of a chartplotter. The GP 32 comes with a 12 Channel WAAS GPS receiver for 3 meters accuracy which will get you right to your favorite fishing holes. With several graphic navigation modes to choose from, you will find this waterproof Furuno GPS unit easy to use and easy to see in almost any lighting condition. In the highway and steering display, you can intuitively see the best way to steer and where the next waypoint is located relative to your ship. Navigation information including ship&#39;s position (in Lat/ Lon or TD&#39;s), speed, course, range/bearing, and ETA/TTG to a targeted waypoint, or MOB position is displayed in large easy to see characters also. Includes display unit, mounting bracket, 6ft power cable, antenna w/10 meter cable, manual. 2 year warranty.  <br /><br />Size 4.9"H x 8.2"W x 3.4"D. (Dimensions include bracket and knobs).  <br /><br />Unit Dimensions 3.9"h x 6.9"w x 3.0"d(without bracket).  <br /><br />Warranty: 2 years parts and labor.', '20081118134404-furuno_gp32_150x.jpg', 0, 0, '4300000', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
