('20081205202619', '20080919070258', '20080919070002', 'Garmin Fisfinder 400C', NULL, NULL, '20081205202619-fishfinder-400cx.jpg', 0, 0, '5200000', NULL, NULL, '<div id="featureTab" class="tabs-container"><br /><br />The versatile Fishfinder 400C has a super bright, high resolution 4-inch display and is great for finding fish in both freshwater and saltwater.\r <h3>Use in Freshwater and Saltwater</h3>\r <br /><br />The 400C is available with a choice of dual beam or dual frequency transducers, so it&rsquo;s readily adaptable for both freshwater and saltwater fishing. The 400 watt (RMS) dual beam version offers a wide fish-finding cone and reaches depths of 900 feet. With the 500 watt (RMS) dual frequency transducer, you can reach a depth of 1,500 feet.\r <h3>Connect with CANet&reg;</h3>\r <br /><br />Fishfinder 400C features a crisp, ultra-bright 4&rdquo; QVGA color display, plus UltraScroll&trade; for screen updates at live-action speeds. It&#39;s also CANet-compatible, so you can share sonar information with plotters located elsewhere in your boat.</div>', '<table id="playlist" border="0" cellspacing="0">\r <tbody>\r <tr>\r <td colspan="2">\r <h3>Physical &amp; Performance:</h3>\r </td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>Unit dimensions, WxHxD:</td>\r <td>5.7" x 5.0" x 2.9" (14.5 x 12.7 x 7.4 cm)</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>Display size, WxH:</td>\r <td>2.6" x 3.3" (6.5 x 8.5 cm)</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>Display resolution, WxH:</td>\r <td>240 x 320 pixels</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>Display type:</td>\r <td>QVGA</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>Weight:</td>\r <td>17.6 (499 g)</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>Waterproof:</td>\r <td>yes (IPX7)</td>\r </tr>\r </tbody>\r </table>\r <table id="playlist" border="0" cellspacing="0">\r <tbody>\r <tr>\r <td colspan="2">\r <h3>Features:</h3>\r </td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>CANet&reg; compatible:</td>\r <td>yes</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>Audible alarms:</td>\r <td>yes</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td>Dual-frequency sonar capable:</td>\r <td>yes</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\