('20081206141659', '20080919070258', '20080919070002', 'Garmin Fishfinder 160Ci', NULL, 'The Fishfinder 160C is a rugged, affordable color sounder for recreational anglers who fish primarily in freshwater lakes.\r <h3>See Fish in Bright Color</h3>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Fish returns and bottom information are clearly shown on the unit&rsquo;s bright, sunlight-readable color display, making it easier for you to scope out your fishing grounds.\r <h3>Pinpoint Your Next Catch</h3>\r <br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br /><br />Fishfinder 160C&#39;s included dual-beam transducer provides excellent shallow-water performance, and the wide viewing angle lets you see fish even off the sides of the boat. The 160C also offers Ultrascroll&trade;, which refreshes the screen with lightning speed so you always see the most up-to-date information. You can manually adjust the gain or set to Auto Gain, which adjusts the level of detail you see automatically.', '20081206150947-FF-160cix.jpg', 0, 0, '3000000', NULL, NULL, 'Other features:\r <ul>\r <li>Automatic display re-scaling on range change (no more vertical lines with range changes)</li>\r <li>Power output: 150 watts (RMS), 1200 watts (peak to peak)</li>\r <li>See-Thru&reg; technology shows weak and strong returns simultaneously</li>\r <li>Unit remembers user settings when it is turned off</li>\r <li>Whiteline shows you how thick the bottom is</li>\r <li>2X and 4X automatic and manual zoom</li>\r <li>Alarms available for fish size, shallow water, deep water and low battery</li>\r <li>Battery voltage indicator</li>\r <li>NMEA output</li>\r </ul>', '<table id="playlist" border="0" cellspacing="0">\r <tbody>\r <tr class="title">\r <td colspan="2">\r <h3>Features:</h3>\r </td>\r </tr>\r <tr class="odd">\r <td>CANet&reg; compatible:</td>\r <td>no</td>\r </tr>\r <tr class="even">\r <td>Audible alarms:</td>\r <td>yes</td>\r </tr>\r <tr class="odd">\r <td>Dual-frequency sonar capable:</td>\r <td>no</td>\r </