('20090213144235', '20081020145021', '20080920095632', 'Icom AT - 130 HF Automatic Antenna Tuner AT-130', NULL, 'AT - 130 HF Automatic Antenna Tuner\r \r Tune in your HF marine world\r \r Suitable for many vessels\r The versatile AT-130 can be used with a variety of vessels, even smaller boats that cannot use a long antenna element. For example, the AT-130 will match a 7 m (23 feet) long wire antenna across the marine band in the 1.6 - 27.5 MHz range.\r \r Automatic tuning\r No manual tuning is needed. Just push the [TUNE] switch on an Icom HF marine transceiver; the AT-130 adjusts the antenna and the transceiver to the minimum SWR in any frequency on an HF marine band. The AT-130 allows you to transmit with strong RF output power, and is perfect for maritime mobile operations.\r \r Weather resistant\r The AT-130 is housed in a durable, completely weather-resistant acrylic case with rubber gaskets. This allows it to be conveniently installed near the antenna element base.\r \r For Icom HF marine transceivers\r Icom&#39;s sophisticated AT-130 easily matches Icom HF marine transceivers. The AT-130 easily interconnects with an Icom HF marine transceiver. AT-130 installation is simple. No adjustments are necessary. Just connect the control cable and antenna wire and go!\r \r Quick tune-up\r Improved tuning performance...the tune-up time is less than 3 seconds in any frequency on an HF marine band. In addition, the AT-130 has 8 convenient memories to store tuning information. Retuning for a memorized frequency takes about 1.5 seconds. This allows you quick trouble-free frequency changes.\r \r Low power tune-up\r The AT-130 emits very little output power (just 300 mW) during the tuning process. This reduces the possibility of causing interference to other stations using the frequency.', '20090213144235-icom-tuner-130x.gif', 0, 0, '4250000', NULL, NULL, NULL, 'Specifications\r \r     * Dimensions: 230(W) x 340(H) x 80(D) mm; 9.1(W) x 13.4(H) x 3.1(D) in (projections not included)\r     * Weight: 2.7 kg; 6.0 lb\r     * Usable Temperature Range: -30C ~ +60C\r     * Rated Voltage: 13.6 V DC +/-15% (negative ground) (supplied from an Icom HF marine transceiver)\r     * Current Drain (at 13.6 V DC): 2 A\r     * Frequency Coverage: 1.6~30 MHz (with the antenna length 7 m (23 ft) or longer)\r     * Input Impedance: 50 ohms (unbalanced)\r     * Max. Input Power: 150 W (PEP)\r     * Input Power During Tuning: 10 W\r     * Auto Tuning Time: 1.5 sec. (returning for a memorized frequency), typically 2~3 sec. (when operating band has been changed)\r     * Auto Tuning Accuracy: VSWR 2.0:1\r     * Insertion Loss: 0.5 dB (with a 50 ohms load, after tuning)\r \r ', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20090213144956', '20081020145021', '20080920095632', 'Icom AT - 140 HF Automatic Antenna Tuner AT-130', NULL, 'Plug and play? With Icom &#39;s IC-M802 marine SSB,it&#39;s about that easy.The AT-140 comes ready for simple antenna cable and power connections. When connected to the IC-M802,the AT-140 automatically bypasses tuning to improve frequency reception. Designed specifically for e-mail and shortwave listening, the AT-140 allows use of the entire antenna for best reception. Get fast frequency access without missing communication opportunities! The AT-140 is housed in a durable,completely weather-resistant acrylic case with rubber gaskets. Install the unit near the antenna element base. While an ideal companion for the IC-M802 SSB,the AT-140 also works well with other Icom marine SSBs like the IC-M710 and the IC-M700PRO. No adjustments are necessary - just connect the SSB control cable and antenna wire and go! The AT-140 automatically stores the matching conditions for up to 45 frequencies. Re-tuning to a memorized frequency takes about 1 second! Tune up in less than 3 seconds on any marine HF band! The AT-140 emits very little output power (just 300mW)during the tuning process,reducing the possibility of interference with other stations.', '20090221170225-Icom_AT-140x.jpg', 0, 0, '5300000', NULL, NULL, '<div id="productAuxDescription" style="display: block;">\r <li>Pre-wired connection points</li>\r <li>Unique Pass-thru tuning</li>\r <li>Weather resistan construction</li>\r <li>Works with Other Icom SSBs</li>\r <li>45 Memories for shorter tuning times</li>\r <li>Quick, low power tune-up</li>\r </div>', NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
