('20081223150429', '20081020144855', '20081223150705', 'Avon R 340', NULL, '<span class="bold">Available in store</span>\r <p class="pt10">With inflatable keels, large buoyancy tubes, and squared-off bows, the Avon Rover Air Deck Inflatable Boats are great performers, providing a stable and comfortable ride. They utilize a unique high pressure air flooring system that when properly inflated results in an extremely light, extremely stiff floor. The lighter weight results in improved performance and fuel economy with small engines. Like the Roll Away Inflatable Boats, the flooring never need be removed to stow the boat: simply deflate it in place and roll the entire boat up. Each Air Deck Inflatable Boat features a rigid fiberglass seat, bow and stern carrying handles, side towing bridle rings, a high profile rubbing strake, lifelines, oarlocks, internal and external oar keepers, and jointed wooden oars. The heavy duty integral marine plywood transom includes an aluminum motor clamp plate, stainless steel transom protection plate, and a transom drain plug. Each Avon Air Deck Inflatable Boat comes with a heavy duty storage valise, bellows air pump, air pressure gauge, repair kit, and an owner&rsquo;s manual. Light gray  <br /><br />SAVE 10% On Avon and Tohatsu packages!*  <br /><br />*10% savings applies to purchase of regularly priced Avon boats and Tohatsu outboards; discounts applies to each when purchased together.', '20081223150429-080310CAT_pg100_4ax.jpg', 0, 1, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL),
('20081223162232', '20081020144855', '20080920095851', 'Bombard Typhoon 420 Inflatable', NULL, 'The Bombard Typhoon range is robust, light and stylish and&nbsp;is&nbsp;ideal for family outings, for a trip out with friends or just to enjoy a spot of sailing in safety. They are simple and quick to set up, whatever floor you choose, and small enough to fit in the boot of your car.  <br /><br />The Typhoon&nbsp;420 has a non-skid wooden floor and aluminium stringers with tie-down rail.  <br /><br />Standard features of the Bombard Typhoon&nbsp;420 are:\r <ul>\r <li>Inflatable Keel </li>\r <li>Non-skid wooden floor </li>\r <li>Aluminium motor plate </li>\r <li>1 self-bailer </li>\r <li>1100 decitex fabric </li>\r <li>Rubbing strake with outlined profile </li>\r <li>2 carrying handles </li>\r <li>2 towing rings </li>\r <li>Reinforced cone ends </li>\r <li>Removable bow bag holdall with velcro fastening </li>\r <li>Carry bag with utility pockets </li>\r <li>2 reinforced aluminium oars </li>\r <li>Foot pump </li>\r <li>Repair kit </li>\r <li>Owners manual </li>\r <li>Bench seat</li>\r </ul>', '20081223162232-ed_4579_typ285x.jpg', 0, 0, NULL, NULL, NULL, NULL, '<table style="height: 616px;" border="0" cellspacing="0" cellpadding="0" width="100%">\r <tbody>\r <tr>\r <td style="background-repeat: no-repeat;" colspan="3" valign="top" bgcolor="#ffffff">\r <table border="0" cellspacing="8" cellpadding="0" width="95%" align="center">\r <tbody>\r <tr>\r <td width="278" valign="top">\r <table border="0" cellspacing="6" cellpadding="0" width="100%">\r <tbody>\r <tr>\r <td colspan="2">\r <table border="0">\r <tbody>\r <tr>\r <td width="49%" align="right" valign="top">\r <h2>Specification</h2>\r </td>\r <td width="51%" valign="top"></td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td align="right" valign="top">Overall Length</td>\r <td align="left" valign="top">4.20m</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td align="right" valign="top">Inside Length</td>\r <td align="left" valign="top">2.94m</td>\r </tr>\r <tr>\r <td align="rig